      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROCK THE NATION NZ (2) looks close to a win having worked forward from wide draws to find the front in his last two outings at this circuit and distance before sticking on well for second, last time going under by a neck. Has the speed to take advantage of this lower draw so can go one better. HANCOCKS HERO (1) improved plenty when second-up last time out, working but digging deep to score by a neck at this circuit and distance. Draws for a cosy run so could go right on with the job. ARENDELLE (4) was fifth from the back row last start at Leeton and had put together a string of seconds here prior. Contender. BULLETIN (8) draws wide but has some good recent performances under the belt including a 2m third last week and a win here last month.",
